                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15242",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This was a documentation issue, and required no code changes. Instead of setting the appropriate invokeArg (which the poster rightly notes will not work, as the ViewRenderer checks against the front controller), the better method is to simply call setNoRender() via init():\n\n{code}\npublic function init()\n{\n    $this->_helper->viewRenderer->setNoRender(true);\n}\n{code}\n\nUpdated docs with r5337.\n",
